text: 10K may refer to: *10000 (number), the natural number following 9999 and preceding 10001 *10K run, a common running race distance *10-K Thirst Quencher, a sports drink *Form 10-K, a form used by the Securities and Exchange Commission *10K, la década robada, Argentine book by Jorge Lanata *10K Plan, a plan by Jerry Brown to attract 10,000 new residents to Oakland, California *10K, character in Z Nation *10K resolution a digital video format having a horizontal resolution of approximately 10,000 pixels ==See also== *K (disambiguation)
title: 10K
